Sports: {Of the 33 households surveyed { 59 different sports played.}
Only eight households said they played no sports. The most popular activity was walking (7) followed by 'keep fit' and golf (5 each) - these activities are readily available in the area. 27 people took part in ball games (golf, tennis, squash, football, hockey, cricket) and croquet and badminton. Other activities mentioned include athletics, judo, dancing, cycling, shooting and snooker.
